  "pride_metadata": {
    "project": {
      "accession": "PXD050739",
      "title": "Regulation of mitochondrial oxidative phosphorylation and venetoclax efficacy in AML via COX4I1",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "Cell signaling pathways are enriched for biological processes crucial for cellular communication, response to external stimuli, and metabolism. Here, we conducted a cell signaling-focused CRISPR screen and identified cytochrome c oxidase subunit 4I1 (COX4I1) as a novel vulnerability in acute myeloid leukemia (AML). Depletion of COX4I1 hindered leukemia cell proliferation and impacted in vivo AML progression. Mechanistically, loss of COX4I1 induced mitochondrial stress and ferroptosis, disrupting mitochondrial ultrastructure and oxidative phosphorylation. CRISPR gene tiling scans, coupled with mitochondrial proteomics, dissected critical regions within COX4I1 essential for leukemia cell survival, providing detailed insights into the mitochondrial Complex IV assembly network. Furthermore, COX4I1 depletion or pharmacological inhibition of Complex IV (using chlorpromazine) synergized with venetoclax, providing a promising avenue for improved leukemia therapy. Our study highlights COX4I1 as a critical mitochondrial checkpoint, offering insights into its functional significance and potential clinical implications.",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "Mitochondrial proteins were digested using the EasyPepTM Mini MS Sample Prep Kit (Thermo Fisher Scientific, USA). After protein digestion, 10ug of peptides were labelled using the 0.1 mg of TMTpro 18-plex Label Reagent Set (Thermo Fisher Scientific, USA) following manufacturer\u2019s instructions. The TMTpro labeled samples were pooled and proceed to peptide clean-up according to the manufacturer\u2019s protocol. Eluted peptides were suspended in 2% acetonitrile (ACN) and 0.2% formic acid (FA) for further LC-MS/MS analysis.LC-MS/MS analysis was performed on an Orbitrap Eclipse Tribrid mass spectrometer (Thermo Fisher Scientific, USA) coupled to an Vanquish Neo UHPLC system (Thermo Fisher Scientific, USA). Peptides were separated on an analytical Aurora Frontier\u2122 column (60 cm \u00d7 75 \u03bcm, 1.7 \u03bcm C18, AUR3-60075C18-CSI, Ion Opticks) with a flow rate of 0.3 \u03bcL/min for a total duration of 130 min and ionized at 1.6 kV in the positive ion mode. The gradient was composed of 6% solvent B (7 min), 6-25% B (88 min), 25-40% B (25 min), 40\u201398% B (1 min) and 98% B (9min); solvent A: 2% ACN and 0.2% FA in water; solvent B: 80% ACN and 0.2% FA. The TMTpro synchronous precursor selection (SPS)-MS3 method coupled with Real-Time Search (RTS) algorithm was used for the analysis. The Uniprot reviewed human database (Swiss-Prot, UP000005640) was imported and trypsin was set as the enzyme for RTS database. MS1 scans were acquired in the Orbitrap at the resolution of 120,000 from 375 to 1,600 m/z, automatic gain control (AGC) setting of 4x105, and maximum injection time of 50 ms. The precursor ions with 2 to 7 positive charges and intensity of >1x104 were isolated in the quadrupole with an isolation window of 0.7 m/z and fragmented with collision-induced dissociation (CID) collision energy of 35%, activation time of 10 ms, and activation Q of 0.25. MS2 scans were acquired in the ion trap using turbo scan rate with AGC setting as standard and maximum injection time of 45 ms. Top 15 SPS fragment ions were selected with a precursor selection range of 200 to 1,400 m/z and fragmented with higher-energy collisional dissociation (HCD) collision energy of 60%. MS3 scans were then acquired in the Orbitrap at the resolution of 50,000 from 100 to 500 m/z, AGC setting of 1x105, and maximum injection time set as auto. Dynamic exclusion was set to 60 s. The temperature of ion transfer tube was 300\u00b0C and the S-lens RF level was set to 30.",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "Raw files were analyzed with Proteome Discoverer 2.5 software based on the Sequest HT algorithm and searched against in silico tryptic digested Uniprot reviewed human database (Swiss-Prot, UP000005640). The maximum missed cleavages was set to 2. Oxidation (M, +15.995 Da) was set as dynamic modification; carbamidomethylation (C, +57.021 Da) and TMTpro (K and peptide N-termini, +304.207 Da) were set as fixed modifications. The precursor mass tolerance was set to 10 ppm, whereas fragment mass tolerance was set to 0.6 Da. The false discovery threshold was set strictly to 0.01 using the Percolator Node validated by q-value. Reporter ion intensities were adjusted by correction factors in all samples according to the TMTpro 18plex Lot Number XE343711 product data sheet (Thermo Fisher Scientific, USA).",
